# Tool Intro Splash — Non-Distort Maximized Layout

All cinematic fullscreen tool intros (`*IntroGate.tsx` + `*-landing.css`) inherit layout from `src/components/tool-intro-splash.css` (via `globals.css`).

## Required shell

```tsx
<div className="{prefix}-fs tool-intro-fs">
  <header className="{prefix}-fs__header">…</header>
  <div className="{prefix}-fs__stage">
    <div className="{prefix}-fs__scene">
      <div className="{prefix}-fs__workspace animation-workspace">
        <div className="{prefix}-fs__card">{/* animation */}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div className="{prefix}-fs__footer">
    <button className="{prefix}-fs__cta">Get Started</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

- Always include `tool-intro-fs` on the root and `animation-workspace` on the workspace.
- Optional aliases: `global-splash-workspace`, `global-splash-card`.
- Keep success badges **inside** `__card` so they are not clipped.

## Global footprint (caps only — no forced width)

| Zone | Standard |
|------|----------|
| Stage / workspace | Flex-centered, `max-height: calc(100vh - 180px)`, `max-width: 100%` |
| Inner `__card` / cardless visual | Tool-owned size, capped with `max-width: 100%`, `max-height: 60vh`, `object-fit: contain`, `margin: 0 auto` |

**Do not** force cards to a fixed width (e.g. `780px` / `width: 95%`). That stretches square/portrait/landscape art.

Tool CSS owns native proportions (`clamp()`, aspect-ratio, fixed preview sizes). Shared CSS only centers, caps, and uniformly zooms.

## Uniform scale-up (no axis distortion)

Root `--splash-zoom` (default `1.1`) enlarges the whole workspace uniformly via `zoom` (transform fallback where needed).

- Opt out or tune per tool: `.xyz-fs.tool-intro-fs { --splash-zoom: 1; }` or `1.2`
- Never use non-uniform `scaleX` / stretched widths to “fill” dead space

## Internal content rules

- Prefer responsive `clamp()` and fluid graphic sizes in tool CSS.
- Use `flex-shrink: 1`, `min-height: 0`, `min-width: 0` on growing regions when needed.
- Avoid entrance animations with large `translateY` past card edges; prefer opacity/scale.
- Never overlap the headline or Get Started / התחל / Начать CTA.

## Multi-card / N-up exceptions

- Side-by-side cards: workspace capped as one unit; each card keeps native size.
- `.nup-fs` keeps multi-column stage rules (`zoom: 1`).

## Checklist for a new tool splash

1. Gate uses `tool-intro-fs` + `animation-workspace`.
2. Card uses natural aspect (tool CSS); no global fixed width.
3. Tune `--splash-zoom` only if the default enlarge is too much/little.
4. Badge inside card; internals don’t spill.
5. i18n CTA keys for en / he / ru.
